  orderNo 98
  title `Declaration of assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 72 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 24-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29588&sectionno=75A&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_75_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every elected candidate for a House of Parliament`
  line `shall, within ninety days from the date on which he makes and subscribes an oath or affirmation,`
  line `according to the form set out for the purpose in the Third Schedule to the Constitution, for taking his seat`
  line `in either House of Parliament, furnish the information, relating to`
  line
  line `(i) the movable and immovable property of which he, his spouse and his dependant children are`
  line `jointly or severally owners or beneficiaries;`
  line
  line `(ii) his liabilities to any public financial institution; and`
  line
  line `(iii) his liabilities to the Central Government or the State Government, to the Chairman of the`
  line `Council of States or the Speaker of the House of the People, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The information under sub-section (1) shall be furnished in such form and in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed in the rules made under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman of the Council of States or the Speaker of the House of the People, as the case may`
  line `be, may make rules for the purposes of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The rules made by the Chairman of the Council of States or the Speaker of the House of the`
  line `People, under sub-section (3) shall be laid, as soon as may be after they are made, before the Council of`
  line `States or the House of the People, as the case may be, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions and shall take effect upon the expiry of`
  line `the said period of thirty days unless they are sooner approved with or without modifications or`
  line `disapproved by the Council of States or the House of the People and where they are so approved, they`
  line `shall take effect on such approval in the form in which they were laid or in such modified form, as the`
  line `case may be, and where they are so disapproved, they shall be of no effect.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairman of the Council of States or the Speaker of the House of the People, as the case may`
  line `be, may direct that any wilful contravention of the rules made under sub-section (3) by an elected`
  line `candidate for a House of Parliament referred to in sub-section (1) may be dealt with in the same manner`
  line `as a breach of privilege of the Council of States or the House of the People, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(i) "immovable property" means the land and includes any building or other structure attached to`
  line `the land or permanently fastened to anything which is attached to the land;`
  line
  line `(ii) "movable property" means any other property which is not the immovable property and`
  line `includes corporeal and incorporeal property of every description;`
  line
  line `(iii) "public financial institution" means a public financial institution within the meaning of`
  line `section 4A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and includes bank;`
  line
  line `(iv) "bank" referred to in clause (iii) means—`
  line
  line `(a) State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(b) subsidiary bank having the meaning assigned to it in clause (K) of section 2 of the State`
  line `Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);`
  line
  line `(c) Regional Rural Bank established under section 3 of the Regional Rural Banks`
  line `Act, 1976 (21 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(d) corresponding new bank having the meaning assigned to it in clause (da) of section 5 of`
  line `the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949); and`
  line
  line `(e) co-operative bank having the meaning assigned to it in clause (cci) of section 5 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) as modified by sub-clause (i) of clause (c) of`
  line `section 56 of that Act; and`
  line
  line `(v) "dependant children" means sons and daughters who have no separate means of earning and`
  line `are wholly dependant on the elected candidate referred to in sub-section (1) for their livelihood.]`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (29589)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 99
  title `Application of Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 42, for sections 76 to 78 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29589&sectionno=76&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `^1[76. Application of Chapter.--This Chapter shall apply only to the elections to the House of the`
  line `People and to the Legislative Assembly of a State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (29590)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 100
  title `Account of election expenses and maximum thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29590&sectionno=77&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every candidate at an election shall,`
  line `either by himself or by his election agent, keep a separate and correct account of all expenditure in`
  line `connection with the election incurred or authorised by him or by his election agent between ^1[the date on which he has been nominated] and the date of declaration of the result thereof, both dates inclusive.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation 1.For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that`
  line
  line `(a) the expenditure incurred by leaders of a political party on account of travel by air or by any`
  line `other means of transport for propagating programme of the political party shall not be deemed to be`
  line `the expenditure in connection with the election incurred or authorised by a candidate of that political`
  line `party or his election agent for the purposes of this sub-section;`
  line
  line `(b) any expenditure incurred in respect of any arrangements made, facilities provided or any other`
  line `act or thing done by any person in the service of the Government and belonging to any of the classes`
  line `mentioned in clause (7) of section 123 in the discharge or purported discharge of his official duty as`
  line `mentioned in the proviso to that clause shall not be deemed to be expenditure in connection with the`
  line `election incurred or authorised by a candidate or by his election agent for the purposes of this`
  line sub-section.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.For the purposes of clause (a) of Explanation 1, the expression leaders of a political`
  line `party, in respect of any election, means,`
  line
  line `(i) where such political party is a recognised political party, such persons not exceeding forty in`
  line `number, and`
  line
  line `(ii) where such political party is other than a recognised political party, such persons not`
  line `exceeding twenty in number,`
  line
  line `whose names have been communicated to the Election Commission and the Chief Electoral Officers of`
  line `the States by the political party to be leaders for the purposes of such election, within a period of seven`
  line `days from the date of the notification for such election published in the Gazette of India or Official`
  line `Gazette of the State, as the case may be, under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a political party may, in the case where any of the persons referred to in clause (i) or, as`
  line `the case may be, in clause (ii) dies or ceases to be a member of such political party, by further`
  line `communication to the Election Commission and the Chief Electoral Officers of the States, substitute new`
  line `name, during the period ending immediately before forty-eight hours ending with the hour fixed for the`
  line `conclusion of the last poll for such election, for the name of such person died or ceased to be a member,`
  line `for the purposes of designating the new leader in his place.]`
  line
  line `(2) The account shall contain such particulars, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The total of the said expenditure shall not exceed such amount as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 1975, s. 6, for certain words (w.r.e.f. 6-8-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 2003, s. 4, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 11-9-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (29591)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 101
  title `Lodging of account with the district election officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29591&sectionno=78&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Every contesting candidate at an`
  line `election shall, within thirty days from the date of election of the returned candidate or, if there are more`
  line `than one returned candidate at the election and the dates of their election are different, the later of those`
  line `two dates, lodge with the ^2[district election officer] an account of his election expenses which shall be a`
  line `true copy of the account kept by him or by his election agent under section 77.`
  line
  line ^3*****
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 78 re-numbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 47 of 1966, s. 36 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 36, ibid., for "returning officer" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 2 of 2004, s. 3 (w.e.f. 29-10-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_78_a:
  sectionId (29592)
  sectionNo 78A
  orderNo 102
  title `Free supply of copies of electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 11-9-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29592&sectionno=78A&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_78_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Government shall, at any election to be held`
  line `for the purposes of constituting the House of the People or the Legislative Assembly of a State, supply,`
  line `free of cost, to the candidates of recognsied political parties such number of copies of the electoral roll, as`
  line `finally published under the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) and such other material`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The material referred to in sub-section (1) shall be supplied,—`
  line
  line `(i) subject to such conditions as may be imposed by the Central Government in consultation with`
  line `the Election Commission with respect to the reduction of the maximum expenditure which may be`
  line `incurred by the candidate under section 77; and`
  line
  line `(ii) through such officers as may be specified by the Election Commission who shall act in`
  line `accordance with such general or special directions as may be given by the Election Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_b:
  sectionId (29593)
  sectionNo 78B
  orderNo 103
  title `Supply of certain items to candidates, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29593&sectionno=78B&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_78_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election Commission shall, at any time`
  line `between the date of publication of the notification calling the election for the purposes of constituting the`
  line `House of the People or the Legislative Assembly of a State and the date on which the poll is to be taken,`
  line `supply or cause to be supplied, such items as the Central Government may, by order, determine in`
  line `consultation with the Election Commission, to the electors in the constituencies concerned or to the`
  line `candidates set up by the recognised political parties.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Election Commission supplies the items to the candidates under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Central Government may, in consultation with the Election Commission, impose conditions with respect`
  line `to the reduction of the maximum expenditure which may be incurred by the candidate under section 77.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of section 39A, this Chapter and clause (hh) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 169, the expression "recognised political party", has the meaning assigned to it in the Election`
  line `Symbols (Reservation and Allotment) Order, 1968.]`
obj_root_law_sections_78_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (29594)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 104
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29594&sectionno=79&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `In this Part and in ^1[Part VII] unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `^2[(a) any reference to a High Court or to the Chief Justice or Judge of a High Court shall, in`
  line `relation to a Union territory having a Court of the Judicial Commissioner, be construed as a reference`
  line `to the said Court of the Judicial Commissioner or to the Judicial Commissioner or any Additional`
  line `Judicial Commissioner, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `^3[(b) "candidate" means a person who has been or claims to have been duly nominated as a candidate at any election;]`
  line
  line `(c) "costs" means all costs, charges and expenses of, or incidental to, a trial of an election`
  line petition;
  line
  line `(d) "electoral right" means the right of a person to stand or not to stand as, or ^4[to withdraw or not`
  line `to withdraw] from being, a candidate, or to vote or refrain from voting at an election;`
  line
  line `^5[(e) "High Court" means the High Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the election`
  line `to which the election petition relates has been held;]`
  line
  line `(f) "returned candidate" means a candidate whose name has been published under section 67 as`
  line `duly elected.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 37, for "Parts VII and VIII" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 40 of 1975, s. 7, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 6-8-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 37, for "to withdraw" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (29595)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 105
  title `Election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29595&sectionno=80&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `No election shall be called in question except by an election petition`
  line `presented in accordance with the provisions of this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80_a:
  sectionId (29596)
  sectionNo 80A
  orderNo 106
  title `High Court to try election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29596&sectionno=80A&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_80_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[80A. High Court to try election petitions.—(1) The Court having jurisdiction to try an election`
  line `petition shall be the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Such jurisdiction shall be exercised ordinarily by a single Judge of the High Court and the Chief`
  line `Justice, shall, from time to time, assign one or more Judges for that purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the High Court consists only of one Judge, he shall try all election petitions`
  line `presented to that Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The High Court in its discretion may, in the interests of justice or convenience, try an election`
  line `petition, wholly or partly, at a place other than the place of seat of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (29597)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 107
  title `Presentation of petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29597&sectionno=81&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) An election petition calling in question any election may be`
  line `presented on one or more of the grounds specified in ^1[sub-section (1)] of section 100 and section 101 to`
  line `the ^2[High Court] by any candidate at such election or any elector ^3[within forty-five days from, but not`
  line `earlier than, the date of election of the returned candidate, or if there are more than one returned candidate`
  line `at the election and the dates of their election are different, the later of those two dates.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, "elector" means a person who was entitled to vote at the election to`
  line `which the election petition relates, whether he has voted at such election or not.`
  line
  line ^4*****
  line
  line `^5[(3) Every election petition shall be accompanied by as many copies thereof as there are respondents`
  line `mentioned in the petition ^6*** and every such copy shall be attested by the petitioner under his own`
  line `signature to be a true copy of the petition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 44, for "sub-sections (1) and (2)" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 39, for "Election Commission" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 44, for certain words (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 47 of 1966, s. 39 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 17 (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  line
  line `6. Certain words omitted by Act 47 of 1966, s. 39 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (29598)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 108
  title `Parties to the petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 45, for section 82 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29598&sectionno=82&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `^1[Parties to the petition.—A petitioner shall join as respondents to his petition—`
  line
  line `(a) where the petitioner, in addition to claiming a declaration that the election of all or any of the`
  line `returned candidates is void, claims a further declaration that he himself or any other candidate has`
  line `been duly elected, all the contesting candidates other than the petitioner, and where no such further`
  line `declaration is claimed, all the returned candidates; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other candidate against whom allegations of any corrupt practice are made in the petition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (29599)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 109
  title `Contents of petition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29599&sectionno=83&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `^1[83. Contents of petition.—(1) An election petition.—`
  line
  line `(a) shall contain a concise statement of the material facts on which the petitioner relies;`
  line
  line `(b) shall set forth full particulars of any corrupt practice that the petitioner alleges, including`
  line `as full a statement as possible of the names of the parties alleged to have committed such corrupt`
  line `practice and the date and place of the commission of each such practice; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall be signed by the petitioner and verified in the manner laid down in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the verification of pleadings:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where the petitioner alleges any corrupt practice, the petition shall also be`
  line `accompanied by an affidavit in the prescribed form in support of the allegation of such corrupt practice`
  line `and the particulars thereof.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any schedule or annexure to the petition shall also be signed by the petitioner and verified in the same manner as the petition].`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 46, ibid., for section 83 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 18 (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (29600)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 110
  title `Relief that may be claimed by the petitioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 47, for section 84 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29600&sectionno=84&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `^1[84. Relief that may be claimed by the petitioner.—A petitioner may, in addition to claiming a`
  line `declaration that the election of all or any of the returned candidates is void, claim a further declaration`
  line `that he himself or any other candidate has been duly elected.]`
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (29601)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 111
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Procedure on receiving petition.] Omitted by Representation of the People (Amendment) Act, 1966 (47 of 1966), s. 40 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29601&sectionno=85&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (29602)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 112
  title `Trial of election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 41, for sections 86 to 92 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29602&sectionno=86&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The High Court shall dismiss an election petition which does`
  line `not comply with the provisions of section 81 or section 82 or section 117.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—An order of the High Court dismissing an election petition under this sub-section shall`
  line `be deemed to be an order made under clause (a) of section 98.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after an election petition has been presented to the High Court, it shall be`
  line `referred to the Judge or one of the Judges who has or have been assigned by the Chief Justice for the trial`
  line `of election petitions under sub-section (2) of section 80A.`
  line
  line `(3) Where more election petitions than one are presented to the High Court in respect of the same`
  line `election, all of them shall be referred for trial to the same Judge who may, in his discretion, try them`
  line `separately or in one or more groups.`
  line
  line `(4) Any candidate not already a respondent shall, upon application made by him to the High Court`
  line `within fourteen days from the date of commencement of the trial and subject to any order as to security`
  line `for costs which may be made by the High Court, be entitled to be joined as a respondent.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section and of section 97, the trial of a petition shall be`
  line `deemed to commence on the date fixed for the respondents to appear before the High Court and answer`
  line `the claim or claims made in the petition.`
  line
  line `(5) The High Court may, upon such terms as to costs and otherwise as it may deem fit, allow the`
  line `particulars of any corrupt practice alleged in the petition to be amended or amplified in such manner as`
  line `may in its opinion be necessary for ensuring a fair and effective trial of the petition, but shall not allow`
  line `any amendment of the petition which will have the effect of introducing particulars of a corrupt practice`
  line `not previously alleged in the petition.`
  line
  line `(6) The trial of an election petition shall, so far as is practicable consistently with the interests of`
  line `justice in respect of the trial, be continued from day to day until its conclusion, unless the High Court`
  line `finds the adjournment of the trial beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be recorded.`
  line
  line `(7) Every election petition shall be tried as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made to`
  line `conclude the trial within six months from the date on which the election petition is presented to the High`
  line `Court for trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (29603)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 113
  title `Procedure before the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29603&sectionno=87&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and of any rules`
  line `made thereunder, every election petition shall be tried by the High Court, as nearly as may be, in`
  line `accordance with the procedure applicable under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) to the trial`
  line `of suits:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court shall have the discretion to refuse, for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `to examine any witness or witnesses if it is of the opinion that the evidence of such witness or witnesses is`
  line `not material for the decision of the petition or that the party tendering such witness or witnesses is doing`
  line `so on frivolous grounds or with a view to delay the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, be deemed to apply in all respects to the trial of an election petition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (29604)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 114
  title `Documentary evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29604&sectionno=93&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any enactment to the contrary, no`
  line `document shall be inadmissible in evidence at the trial of an election petition on the ground that it is not`
  line `duly stamped or registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (29605)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 115
  title `Secrecy of voting not to be infringed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2003, s. 4 (w.e.f. 28-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29605&sectionno=94&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `No witness or other person shall be required to state for`
  line `whom he has voted at an election:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that this section shall not apply to such witness or other person where he has voted by`
  line `open ballot.]`
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (29606)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 116
  title `Answering of criminating questions and certificate of indemnity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29606&sectionno=95&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `[(1) No witness shall be`
  line `excused from answering any question as to any matter relevant to a matter in issue in the trial of an`
  line `election petition upon the ground that the answer to such question may criminate or may tend to criminate`
  line `him, or that it may expose or may tend to expose him to any penalty or forfeiture:`
  line
  line `Provided that`
  line
  line `(a) a witness, who answers truly all questions which he is required to answer shall be entitled to`
  line `receive a certificate of indemnity from ^1[the High Court]; and`
  line
  line `(b) an answer given by a witness to a question put by or before ^1[the High] Court shall not, except`
  line `in the case of any criminal proceeding for perjury in respect of the evidence, be admissible in`
  line `evidence against in any civil or criminal proceeding.`
  line
  line `(2) When a certificate of indemnity has been granted to any witness, it may be pleaded by him in any`
  line `Court and shall be a full and complete defence to or upon any charge under Chapter IXA of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860), or Part VII of this Act arising out of the matter to which such certificate relates,`
  line `but it shall not be deemed to relieve him from any disqualification in connection with an election imposed`
  line `by this Act or any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (29607)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 117
  title `Expenses of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29607&sectionno=96&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `The reasonable expenses incurred by any person in attending to give`
  line `evidence may be allowed by ^1[the High Court] to such person and shall, unless ^1[the High Court]`
  line `otherwise directs, be deemed to be part of the costs.`
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (29608)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 118
  title `Recrimination when seat claimed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29608&sectionno=97&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) When in an election petition a declaration that any`
  line `candidate other than the returned candidate has been duly elected is claimed, the returned candidate or`
  line `any other party may give evidence to prove that the election of such candidate would have been void if he`
  line `had been the returned candidate and a petition had been presented calling in question his election:`
  line
  line `Provided that the returned candidate or such other party, as aforesaid shall not be entitled to give such`
  line `evidence unless he has, within fourteen days from the date of ^2[commencement of the trial], given notice`
  line `to ^1[the High Court] of his intention to do so and has also given the security and the further security`
  line `referred to in sections 117 and 118 respectively.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notice referred to in sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by the statement and ^3***`
  line `particulars required by section 83 in the case of an election petition and shall be signed and verified in`
  line `like manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 52, for "the publication of the election petition under section 90" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `3. The words “list of” omitted by s. 52, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (29609)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 119
  title `Decision of the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29609&sectionno=98&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `98. Decision of the High Court.^1[the High Court].--(1) At the conclusion of the trial of an election petition ^1[the High`
  line `Court] shall make an order.--`
  line
  line `(a) dismissing the election petition; or`
  line
  line `(b) declaring the election of ^2[all or any of the returned candidates] to be void; or`
  line
  line `(c) declaring the election of ^2[all or any of the returned candidates] to be void and the petitioner or`
  line `any other candidate to have been duly elected. ^3***`
  line
  line `^4**** *`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line `1,. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for "the returned candidate" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `3. The word "or" omitted by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by s. 53, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 54, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `6. Certain words omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 29 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (29610)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 120
  title `Other orders to be made by the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29610&sectionno=99&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Other orders to be made by ^1]the High Court].--(1) At the time of making an order under`
  line `section 98 ^1[the High Court] shall also make an order`
  line
  line `^2[(a) where any charge is made in the petition of any corrupt practice having been committed at`
  line `the election, recording`
  line
  line `(i) finding whether any corrupt practice has or has not been proved to have been committed`
  line `^3*** at the election, and the nature of that corrupt practice; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the names of all persons, if any, who have been proved at the trial to have been guilty of`
  line `any corrupt practice and the nature of that practice; and]`
  line
  line `(b) fixing the total amount of cost payable, and specifying the persons by and to whom costs shall`
  line `be paid:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^4[a person who is not a party to the petition shall not be named] in the order under`
  line `sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) unless`
  line
  line `(a) he has been given notice to appear before ^1[the High Court] and to show cause why he should`
  line `not be so named; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he appears in pursuance of the notice, he has been given an opportunity of cross-examining`
  line `any witness who has already been examined by ^1[the High Court] and has given evidence against him,`
  line `of calling evidence in his defence and of being heard.`
  line
  line `^5(2) In this section and in section 100, the expression agent has the same meaning as in`
  line `section 123.]`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 54, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Certain words omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 29 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 54, for "no person shall be named" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 54, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (29611)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 121
  title `Grounds for declaring election to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29611&sectionno=100&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2)`
  line of
  line ^2
  line `[the High court] is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on the date of his election a returned candidate was not qualified, or was disqualified, to`
  line `be chosen to fill the seat under the Constitution or this Act ^3`
  line `[or the Government of Union Territories`
  line `Act, 1963 (20 of 1963)]; or`
  line
  line `(b) that any corrupt practice has been committed by a returned candidate or his election agent or`
  line `by any other person with the consent of a returned candidate or his election agent; or`
  line
  line `(c) that any nomination has been improperly rejected; or`
  line
  line `(d) that the result of the election, in so far as it concerns a returned candidate, has been materially`
  line affected--
  line
  line `(i) by the improper acceptance or any nomination, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by any corrupt practice committed in the interests of the returned candidate ^4`
  line `[by an agent`
  line `other than his election agent], or`
  line
  line `(iii) by the improper reception, refusal or rejection of any vote or the reception of any vote`
  line `which is void, or`
  line
  line `(iv) by any non-compliance with the provisions of the Constitution or of this Act or of any`
  line `rules or orders made under this Act,`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[the High Court] shall declare the election of the returned candidate to be void.]`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(2)] If in the opinion of ^2`
  line `[the High Court], a returned candidate has been guilty by an agent, other`
  line `than his election agent, of any corrupt practice ^6`
  line `*** but ^2`
  line `[the High Court] is satisfied`
  line
  line `(a) that no such corrupt practice was committed at the election by the candidate or his election`
  line `agent, and every such corrupt practice was committed contrary to the orders, and ^7`
  line `[without the`
  line `consent], of the candidate or his election agent;`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) that the candidate and his election agent took all reasonable means for preventing the`
  line `commission of corrupt ^9*** practices at the election; and`
  line
  line `(d) that in all other respects the election was free from any corrupt ^9*** practice on the part of`
  line `the candidate or any of his agents,`
  line
  line `then ^2`
  line `[the High Court] may decide that the election of the returned candidate is not void.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 1963, s. 57 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 13-5-1963).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 30, for certain words (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-section (3) re-numbered as sub-section (2) by Act 27 of 1956, s. 55 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `6. The words and figures "specified in section 123" omitted by s. 55, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `7. Clause (b) omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 30 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 55, ibid., for "without the sanction or connivance" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `9. The words "or illegal" omitted by Act 27 of 1956, s. 55 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (29612)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 122
  title `Grounds for which a candidate other than the returned candidate may be declared to have been elected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29612&sectionno=101&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `If any person who has lodged a petition has, in addition to calling in question the election`
  line `of the returned candidate, claimed a declaration that he himself or any other candidate has been duly`
  line `elected and ^1`
  line `[the High Court] is of opinion—`
  line
  line `(a) that in fact the petitioner or such other candidate received a majority of the valid votes; or`
  line
  line `(b) that but for the votes obtained by the returned candidate by corrupt ^2`
  line `*** practices the`
  line `petitioner or such other candidate would have obtained a majority of the valid votes,`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[the High Court] shall after declaring the election of the returned candidate to be void declare the`
  line `petitioner or such other candidate, as the case may be, to have been duly elected.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `. The words "or illegal" omitted by Act 27 of 1956, s. 56 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (29613)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 123
  title `Procedure in case of an equality of votes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29613&sectionno=102&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `If during the trial of an election petition it appears`
  line `that there is an equality of votes between any candidates at the election and that the addition of a vote`
  line `would entitle any of those candidates to be declared elected, then—`
  line
  line `(a) any decision made by the returning officer under the provisions of this Act shall, in so far as it`
  line `determines the question between those candidates, be effective also for the purposes of the petition;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) in so far as that question is not determined by such a decision ^1`
  line `[the High Court] shall decide`
  line `between them by lot and proceed as if the one on whom the lot then falls had received an additional`
  line vote.
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (29614)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 124
  title `Communication of orders of the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 43, for s. 103 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29614&sectionno=103&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `^1[103. Communication of orders of the High Court— The High Court shall, as soon as may be`
  line `after the conclusion of the trial of an election petition, intimate the substance of the decision to the`
  line `Election Commission and the Speaker or Chairman, as the case may be, of the House of Parliament or of`
  line `the State Legislature concerned and, as soon as may be thereafter, shall send to the Election Commission`
  line `an authenticated copy of the decision].`
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (29615)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 125
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29615&sectionno=104&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `[Difference of opinion among the members of the Tribunal.] Omitted by the Representation of`
  line `the People (Second Amendment) Act, 1956 (27 of 1956), s. 57 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (29616)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 126
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Orders of the Tribunal to be final and conclusive]. [Omitted by s. 58, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29616&sectionno=105&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (29617)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 127
  title `Transmission of order to the appropriate authority, etc., and its publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29617&sectionno=106&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `As soon as`
  line `may be after the receipt of any order made by ^1`
  line `[the High Court] under section 98 or section 99, the`
  line `Election Commission shall forward copies of the order to the appropriate authority and, in the case where`
  line `such order relates to an election ^2`
  line `*** to a House of Parliament or to an election to the House or a House`
  line `of the Legislature of a State, also to the Speaker or Chairman, as the case may be, of the House concerned`
  line `and ^3`
  line `[shall cause the order to be published--`
  line
  line `(a) where the order relates to an election to a House of Parliament, in the Gazette of India as well`
  line `as in the Official Gazette of the State concerned; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the order relates to an election to the House or a House of the Legislature of the State,`
  line `in the Official Gazette of the State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 42, for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. The brackets and words "(other than a primary election)" omitted by Act 27 of 1956, s. 59 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 59, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (29618)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 128
  title `Effect of orders of the High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29618&sectionno=107&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `^1[107. Effect of orders of the High Court ^2`
  line `[(1) Subject to the provisions contained in`
  line `Chapter IVA relating to the stay of operation of an order of the High Court under section 98 or section 99,`
  line `every such order shall take effect as soon as it is pronounced by the High Court.]`
  line
  line `(2) Where by an order under section 98 the election of a returned candidate is declared to be void,`
  line `acts and proceedings in which that returned candidate has, before the date thereof, participated as a`
  line `member of Parliament or as a member of the Legislature of a State shall not be invalidated by reason of`
  line `that order, nor shall such candidate be subjected to any liability or penalty on the ground of such`
  line participation.]
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 60, for section 107 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (29619)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 129
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29619&sectionno=108&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `[Withdrawal of petitions before appointment of Tribunal]. Omitted by the Representation of the`
  line `People (Amendment) Act, 1966 (47 of 1966), s. 45 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (29620)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 130
  title `Withdrawal of election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 46, for sections 109 and 110 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29620&sectionno=109&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `^1[109. Withdrawal of election petitions.--(1) An election petition may be withdrawn only by leave`
  line `of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application for withdrawal is made under sub-section (1), notice thereof fixing a date for`
  line `the hearing of the application shall be given to all other parties to the petition and shall be published in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (29621)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 131
  title `Procedure for withdrawal of election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29621&sectionno=110&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) If there are more petitioners than one, no`
  line `application to withdraw an election petition shall be made except with the consent of all the petitioners.`
  line
  line `(2) No application for withdrawal shall be granted if, in the opinion of the High Court, such`
  line `application has been induced by any bargain or consideration which ought not to be allowed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the application is granted—`
  line
  line `(a) the petitioner shall be ordered to pay the costs of the respondents there to incurred or`
  line `such portion thereof as the High Court may think fit;`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court shall direct that the notice of withdrawal shall be published in the`
  line `Official Gazette and in such other manner as it may specify and thereupon the notice shall be`
  line `published accordingly;`
  line
  line `(c) a person who might himself have been a petitioner may, within fourteen days of`
  line `such publication, apply to be substituted as petitioner in place of the party withdrawing, and upon`
  line `compliance with the conditions, if any, as to security, shall be entitled to be so substituted and to`
  line `continue the proceedings upon such terms as the High Court may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (29622)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 132
  title `Report of withdrawal by the High Court to the Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29622&sectionno=111&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `When an application`
  line `for withdrawal is granted by ^1`
  line `[the High Court] and no person has been substituted as petitioner under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (3) of section 110, in place of the party withdrawing, ^1`
  line `[the High Court] shall`
  line `report the fact to the Election Commission ^2`
  line `[and thereupon the Election Commission shall publish the`
  line `report in the Official Gazette].`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 47, ibid., for "the Tribunal" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 61 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (29623)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 133
  title `Abatement of election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 48, for sections 112 to 115 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29623&sectionno=112&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `^1[112. Abatement of election petitions.—(1) An election petition shall abate only on the death or a`
  line `sole petitioner or of the survivor of several petition.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an election petition abates under sub-section (1), the High Court shall cause the fact to be`
  line `published in such manner as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who might himself have been a petitioner may, within fourteen days of such`
  line `publication, apply to be substituted as petitioner and upon compliance with the conditions, if any, as`
  line `security, shall be entitled to be so substituted and to continue the proceedings upon such terms as the High`
  line `Court may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (29624)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 134
  title `Abatement or substitution on death of respondent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 49, for the Tribunal (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29624&sectionno=116&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `If before the conclusion of the trial of an`
  line `election petition, the sole respondent dies or gives notice that he does not intend to oppose the petition or`
  line `any of the respondents dies or gives such notice and there is no other respondent who is opposing the`
  line `petition, ^1`
  line `[the High Court] shall cause notice of such event to be published in the Official Gazette, and`
  line `thereupon any person who might have been a petitioner may, within fourteen days of such publication,`
  line `apply to be substituted in place of such respondent to oppose the petition, and shall be entitled to continue`
  line `the proceedings upon such terms as ^1`
  line `[the High Court] may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_a:
  sectionId (29625)
  sectionNo 116A
  orderNo 135
  title `Appeals to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29625&sectionno=116A&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_116_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 , ^2[116A. Appeals to Supreme Court—(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, an appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court on any question (whether of law or fact)`
  line `from every order made by a High Court under section 98 or section 99.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this Chapter shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the order of the High Court under section 98 or section 99:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within such`
  line period.
obj_root_law_sections_116_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 62 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 50, for sections 116A and 116B (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_b:
  sectionId (29626)
  sectionNo 116B
  orderNo 136
  title `Stay of operation of order of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29626&sectionno=116B&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_116_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application may be made to the High`
  line `Court for stay of operation of an order made by the High Court under section 98 or section 99 before the`
  line `expiration of the time allowed for appealing therefrom and the High Court may, on sufficient cause being`
  line `shown and on such terms and conditions as it may think fit, stay the operation of the order; but no`
  line `application for stay shall be made to the High Court after an appeal has been preferred to the Supreme`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(2) Where an appeal has been preferred against an order made under section 98 or section 99, the`
  line `Supreme Court may, on sufficient cause being shown and on such terms and conditions as it may think`
  line `fit, stay the operation of the order appealed from.`
  line
  line `(3) When the operation of an order is stayed by the High Court or, as the case may be, the Supreme`
  line `Court, the order shall be deemed never to have taken effect under sub-section (1) of section 107; and a`
  line `copy of the stay order shall immediately be sent by the High Court or, as the case may be, the Supreme`
  line `Court, to the Election Commission and the Speaker or Chairman, as the case may be, of the House of`
  line `Parliament or of the State Legislature concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116_c:
  sectionId (29627)
  sectionNo 116C
  orderNo 137
  title `Procedure in appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29627&sectionno=116C&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_116_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and of the rules, if any, made`
  line `thereunder, every appeal shall be heard and determined by the Supreme Court as nearly as may be in`
  line `accordance with the procedure applicable to the hearing and determination of an appeal from any final`
  line `order passed by a High Court in the exercise of its original civil jurisdiction; and all the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), and the Rules of the Court, (including provisions as to the`
  line `furnishing of security and the execution of any order of the Court) shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to such appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as an appeal is decided, the Supreme Court shall intimate the substance of the decision to`
  line `the Election Commission and the Speaker or Chairman, as the case may be, of the House of Parliament or`
  line `of the State Legislature concerned and as soon as may be thereafter shall send to the Election Commission`
  line `an authenticated copy of the decision; and upon its receipt, the Election Commission shall--`
  line
  line `(a) forward copies thereof to the authorities to which copies of the order of the High Court were`
  line `forwarded under section 160; and`
  line
  line `(b) cause the decision to be published in the Gazette or Gazettes in which that order was`
  line `published under the said section.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_116_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (29628)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 138
  title `Security for costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 51, for sections 117, 118, 119, 119A and 120 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29628&sectionno=117&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `^1[117. Security for costs.--(1) At the time of presenting an election petition, the petitioner shall`
  line `deposit in the High Court in accordance with the rules of the High Court a sum of two thousand rupees as`
  line `security for the costs of the petition.`
  line
  line `(2) During the course of the trial of an election petition, the High Court may, at any time, call upon`
  line `the petitioner to give such further security for costs as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (29629)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 139
  title `Security for costs from a respondent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29629&sectionno=118&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to be joined as a respondent`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 86 unless he has given such security for costs as the High Court may`
  line direct.
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (29630)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 140
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29630&sectionno=119&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Costs shall be in the discretion of the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a petition is dismissed under clause (a) of section 98, the returned candidate shall`
  line `be entitled to the costs incurred by him in contesting the petition and accordingly the High Court shall`
  line `make an order for costs in favour of the returned candidate].`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (29631)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 141
  title `Payment of costs out of security deposits and return of such deposits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29631&sectionno=121&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in any order as`
  line `to costs under the provisions of this Part there is a direction for payment of costs by any party to any`
  line `person, such costs shall, if they have not been already paid, be paid in full, or so far as possible, out of the`
  line `security deposit and the further security deposit, if any, made by such party under this Part, on an`
  line `application made in writing in that behalf ^1`
  line `[within a period of one year, from the date of such order] to`
  line ^2
  line `[the High Court] by the person in whose favour the costs have been awarded.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is any balance left of any of the said security deposits after payment under sub-section (1)`
  line `of the costs referred to in that sub-section, such balance, or where no costs have been awarded or no`
  line `application as aforesaid has been made within the said period of ^3`
  line `[one year] the whole of the said security`
  line `deposits may, on an application made in that behalf in writing to ^2`
  line `[the High Court] by the person by`
  line `whom the deposits have been made, or if such person dies after making such deposits by the legal`
  line `representative of such person, be returned to the said person or to his legal representative, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 34, for certain words (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 52, for "the Election Commission" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 34, for "six months" (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (29632)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 142
  title `Execution of orders as to costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes `251. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29632&sectionno=122&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `Any order as to costs under the provisions of this part may be`
  line `produced before the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction any person directed by such order to pay any sum of money has a place of residence or`
  line `business, or where such place is within a presidency-town, before the court of small causes having`
  line `jurisdiction there, and such court shall execute the order or cause the same to be executed in the same`
  line `manner and by the same procedure as if it were a decree for the payment of money made by itself in a`
  line `suit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such costs or any portion thereof may be recovered by an application made`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 121, no application shall lie under this section ^1`
  line `[within a period of one`
  line `year from the date of such order] unless it is for the recovery of the balance of any costs which has been`
  line `left unrealised after an application has been made under that sub-section owing to the insufficiency of the`
  line `amount of the security deposits referred to in that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (29633)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 143
  title `Corrupt practices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29633&sectionno=123&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `^1 , ^2The following shall be deemed to be corrupt practices for the purposes of`
  line `this Act:--`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(1) Bribery that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(A) any gift, offer or promise by a candidate or his agent or by any other person with the`
  line `consent of a candidate or his election agent of any gratification, to any person whomsoever, with`
  line `the object, directly or indirectly of inducing--`
  line
  line `(a) a person to stand or not to stand as, or ^4`
  line `[to withdraw or not to withdraw] from being a`
  line `candidate at an election, or`
  line
  line `(b) an elector to vote or refrain from voting at an election, or as a reward to`
  line
  line `(i) a person for having so stood or not stood, or for ^5`
  line `[having withdrawn or not having`
  line `withdrawn] his candidature; or`
  line
  line `(ii) an elector for having voted or refrained from voting;`
  line
  line `(B) the receipt of, or agreement to receive, any gratification, whether as a motive or a`
  line reward--
  line
  line `(a) by a person for standing or not standing as, or for ^6`
  line `[withdrawing or not withdrawing]`
  line `from being, a candidate; or`
  line
  line `(b) by any person whomsoever for himself or any other person for voting or refraining`
  line `from voting, or inducing or attempting to induce any elector to vote or refrain from voting, or`
  line `any candidate ^4`
  line `[to withdraw or not to withdraw] his candidature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause the term "gratification" is not restricted to`
  line `pecuniary gratifications or gratifications estimable in money and it includes all forms of entertainment`
  line `and all forms of employment for reward but it does not include the payment of any expenses`
  line `bona fide incurred at, or for the purpose of, any election and duly entered in the account of election`
  line `expenses referred to in section 78.]`
  line
  line `(2) Undue influence, that is to say, any direct or indirect interference or attempt to interfere on the`
  line `part of the candidate or his agent, or of any other person ^7`
  line `[with the consent of the candidate or his`
  line `election agent]], with the free exercise of any electoral right:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of this clause any such person as is`
  line `referred to therein who--`
  line
  line `(i) the reatens any candidate or any elector, or any person in whom a candidate or an`
  line `elector is interested, with injury of any kind including social ostracism and ex-communication`
  line `or expulsion from any caste or community; or`
  line
  line `(ii) induces or attempts to induce a candidate or an elector to believe that he, or any`
  line `person in whom he is interested, will become or will be rendered an object of divine`
  line `displeasure or spiritual censure,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to interfere with the free exercise of the electoral right of such candidate or elector within`
  line `the meaning of this clause;`
  line
  line `(b) a declaration of public policy, or a promise of public action, or the mere exercise of a legal`
  line `right without intent to interfere with an electoral right, shall not be deemed to be interference within`
  line `the meaning of this clause.`
  line
  line `^8[(3) The appeal by a candidate or his agent or by any other person with the consent of a candidate or his election agent to vote or refrain from voting for any person on the ground of his religion, race, caste, community or language or the use of, or appeal to religious symbols or the use of, or appeal to, national symbols, such as the national flag or the national emblem, for the furtherance of the prospects of the election of that candidate or for prejudicially affecting the election of any candidate:`
  line
  line `^9[Provided that no symbol allotted under this Act to a candidate shall be deemed to be a religious`
  line `symbol or a national symbol for the purposes of this clause.]`
  line
  line `(3A) The promotion of, or attempt to promote, feelings of enmity or hatred between different classes`
  line `of the citizens of India on grounds of religion, race, caste, community, or language, by a candidate or his`
  line `agent or any other person with the consent of a candidate or his election agent for the furtherance of the`
  line `prospects of the election of that candidate or for prejudicially affecting the election of any candidate.]`
  line
  line `^10[(3B) The propagation of the practice or the commission of sati or its glorification by a candidate or`
  line `his agent or any other person with the consent of the candidate or his election agent for the furtherance of`
  line `the prospects of the election of that candidate or for prejudicially affecting the election of any candidate.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "sati" and "glorification" in relation to sati shall`
  line `have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the Commission of Sati (Prevention)`
  line `Act, 1987 (3 of 1988).`
  line
  line `(4) The publication by a candidate or his agent or by any other person ^11`
  line `[with the consent of a`
  line `candidate or his election agent], of any statement of fact which is false, and which he either believes to be`
  line `false or does not believe to be true, in relation to the personal character or conduct of any candidate or in`
  line `relation to the candidature, or withdrawal, ^12`
  line `*** of any candidate, being a statement reasonably calculated`
  line `to prejudice the prospects of that candidates election.`
  line
  line `(5) The hiring or procuring, whether on payment or otherwise, of any vehicle or vessle by a candidate`
  line `or his agent or by any other person ^11`
  line `[with the consent of a candidate or his election agent] ^13`
  line `[or the use of`
  line `such vehicles or vessel for the free conveyance] of any elector (other than the candidate himself, the`
  line `members of his family or his agent) to or from any polling station provided under section 25 or a place`
  line `fixed under sub-section (1) of section 29 for the poll:`
  line
  line `Provided that the hiring of a vehicle or vessel by an elector or by several electors at their joint costs`
  line `for the purpose of conveying him or them to and from any such polling station or place fixed for the poll`
  line `shall not be deemed to be a corrupt practice under this clause if the vehicle or vessel so hired is a vehicle`
  line `or vessel not propelled by mechanical power:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the use of any public transport vehicle or vessel or any tramcar or railway`
  line `carriage by any elector at his own cost for the purpose of going to or coming from any such polling`
  line `station or place fixed for the poll shall not be deemed to be a corrupt practice under this clause.`
  line
  line `Explanation.In this clause, the expression vehicle means any "vehicle" used or capable of being`
  line `used for the purpose of road transport, whether propelled by mechanical power or otherwise and whether`
  line `used for drawing other vehicles or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(6) The incurring or authorising of expenditure in contravention of section 77.`
  line
  line `(7) The obtaining or procuring or a betting or attempting to obtain or procure by a candidate or his`
  line `agent or, by any other person ^11`
  line `[with the consent of a candidate or his election agent], any assistance (other`
  line `than the giving of vote) for the furtherance of the prospects of that candidates election, ^14`
  line `[from any person`
  line `whether or not in the service of the Government] and belonging to any of the following classes,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) gazetted officers;`
  line
  line `(b) stipendiary judges and magistrates;`
  line
  line `(c) members of the armed forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(d) members of the police forces;`
  line
  line `(e) excise officers;`
  line
  line ^15
  line `[(f) revenue officers other than village revenue officers known as lambardars malguzars, patels,`
  line `deshmukhs or by any other name, whose duty is to collect land revenue and who are remunerated by a`
  line `share of, or commission on, the amount of land revenue collected by them but who do not discharge`
  line `any police functions; and`
  line
  line `(g) such other class of persons in the service of the Government as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line ^9
  line `[Provided that where any person, in the service of the Government and belonging to any of the`
  line `classes aforesaid, in the discharge or puported discharge of his official duty, makes any arrangements or`
  line `provides any facilities or does any other act or thing, for, to, or in relation to, any candidate or his agent or`
  line `any other person acting with the consent of the candidate or his election agent, (whether by reason of the`
  line `office held by the candidate or for any other reason), such arrangements facilities or act or thing shall not`
  line `be deemed to be assistance for the furtherance of the prospects of that candidates election];`
  line
  line ^16
  line `[(h) class of persons in the service of a local authority, university, government company or`
  line `institution or concern or undertaking appointed or deputed by the Election Commission in connection`
  line `with the conduct of elections.]`
  line
  line ^17
  line `[(8) Booth capturing by a candidate or his agent or other person.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--(1) In this section the expression "agent" includes an election agent, a polling agent`
  line `and any person who is held to have acted as an agent in connection with the election with the consent of`
  line `the candidate.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of clause (7), a person shall be deemed to assist in the furtherance of the`
  line `prospects of a candidate's election if he acts as an election agent ^18`
  line `*** of that candidate.`
  line
  line ^19
  line `[(3) For the purposes of clause (7), notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, the`
  line `publication in the Official Gazette of the appointment, resignation, termination of service, dismissal or`
  line `removal from service of a person in the service of the Central Government (including a person serving in`
  line `connection with the administration of a Union territory) or of a State Government shall be conclusive`
  line proof
  line
  line `(i) of such appointment, resignation, termination of service, dismissal or removal from service, as`
  line `the case may be, and`
  line
  line `(ii) where the date of taking effect of such appointment, resignation, termination of service,`
  line `dismissal or removal from service, as the case may be, is stated in such publication, also of the fact`
  line `that such person was appointed with effect from the said date, or in the case of resignation,`
  line `termination of service, dismissal or removal from service, such person ceased to be in such service`
  line `with effect from the said date.]`
  line
  line ^20
  line `[(4) For the purposes of clause (8), "booth capturing" shall have the same meaning as in`
  line `section 135A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 65, for the heading "CORRUPT AND ILLEGAL PRACTICES AND ELECTROAL OFFENCES"`
  line `(w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for "the heading Chapters I and II" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 36, for clause (1) (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 53, for "to withdraw" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for "having withdrawn" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for "withdrawing" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 36 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 23, for clause (3) (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 40 of 1975, s. 8 (w.e.f. 6-8-1975).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 3 of 1988, s. 19 (w.e.f. 21-3-1988).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 36 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `12. The words "or retirement from contest" omitted by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 53, for "the conveyance" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966)`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 41 of 2009, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-2010).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 36, for sub-clause (f) (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `16. Ins. by Act 41 of 2009, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-2-2010).`
  line
  line `17. Ins. by Act 1 of 1989, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  line
  line `18. The words "or a polling agent or a counting agent" omitted by Act 47 of 1966, s. 53 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `19. Added by Act 40 of 1975, s. 8 (w.e.f. 6-8-1975).`
  line
  line `20. Ins. by Act 1 of 1989, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-3-1989)`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (29634)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 144
  title `Promoting enmity between classes in connection with election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 24 (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29634&sectionno=125&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `^1[125. Promoting enmity between classes in connection with election.--Any person who in`
  line `connection with an election under this Act promotes or attempts to promote on grounds of religion, race,`
  line `caste, community or language, feelings of enmity or hatred, between different classes of the citizens of`
  line `India shall he punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_125_a:
  sectionId (29710)
  sectionNo 125A
  orderNo 145
  title `Penalty for filing false affidavit, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by 72 of 2002, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-8-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29710&sectionno=125A&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_125_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[125A . Penalty for filing false affidavit, etc.—A candidate who himself or through his proposer,`
  line `with intent to be elected in an election,—`
  line
  line `(i) fails to furnish information relating to sub-section (1) of section 33A; or`
  line
  line `(ii) give false information which he knows or has reason to believe to be false; or`
  line
  line `(iii) conceals any information,`
  line
  line `in his nomination paper delivered under sub-section (1) of section 33 or in his affidavit which is required`
  line `to be delivered under sub-section (2) of section 33A, as the case may be, shall, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (29711)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 146
  title `Prohibition of public meetings during period of forty-eight hours ending with hour fixed for conclusion of poll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 10, for section 126 (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29711&sectionno=126&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `^1[126. Prohibition of public meetings during period of forty-eight hours ending with hour fixed`
  line `for conclusion of poll.--`
  line `(1) No person shall`
  line
  line `(a) convene, hold, attend, join or address any public meeting or procession in connection with`
  line `an election; or`
  line
  line `(b) display to the public any election matter by means of cinematograph, television or other`
  line `similar apparatus; or`
  line
  line `(c) propagate any election matter to the public by holding, or by arranging the holding of, any`
  line `musical concert or any theatrical performance or any other entertainment or amusement with a`
  line `view to attracting the members of the public thereto,`
  line
  line `in any polling area during the period of forty-eight hours ending with the hour fixed for the conclusion of`
  line `the poll for any election in that polling area.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section, the expression "election matter" means any matter intended or calculated to`
  line `influence or affect the result of an election.]`
obj_root_law_sections_126_a:
  sectionId (29712)
  sectionNo 126A
  orderNo 147
  title `Restriction on publication and dissemination of result of exit polls, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2009, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29712&sectionno=126A&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_126_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[@b^126A. Restriction on publication and dissemination of result of exit polls, etc.—(1) No person`
  line `shall conduct any exit poll and publish or publicise by means of the print or electronic media or`
  line `disseminate in any other manner, whatsoever, the result of any exit poll during such period, as may be`
  line `notified by the Election Commission in this regard.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Election Commission shall, by a general order, notify the`
  line `date and time having due regard to the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) in case of a general election, the period may commence from the beginning of the hours fixed`
  line `for poll on the first day of poll and continue till half an hour after closing of the poll in all the States`
  line `and Union territories;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of a bye-election or a number of bye-elections held together, the period may`
  line `commence from the beginning of the hours fixed for poll on and from the first day of poll and`
  line `continue till half an hour after closing of the poll:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a number of bye-elections held together on different days, the period may`
  line `commence from the beginning of the hours fixed for poll on the first day of poll and continue till half`
  line `an hour after closing of the last poll.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who contravenes the provisions of this section shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to two years or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `Explanation@/ib@.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) exit poll means an opinion survey respecting how electors have voted at an election or`
  line `respecting how all the electors have performed with regard to the identification of a political party or`
  line `candidate in an election;`
  line
  line `(b) electronic media includes internet, radio and television including Internet Protocol`
  line `Television, satellite, terrestrial or cable channels, mobile and such other media either owned by the`
  line `Government or private person or by both;`
  line
  line `(c) print media includes any newspaper, magazine or periodical, poster, placard, handbill or any`
  line `other document;`
  line
  line `(d) dissemination includes publication in any print media or broadcast or display on any`
  line `electronic media.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_b:
  sectionId (29713)
  sectionNo 126B
  orderNo 148
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29713&sectionno=126B&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_126_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under sub-section (2) of section 126A has`
  line `been committed by a company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge`
  line `of, and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the`
  line `company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_126_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (29714)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 149
  title `Disturbances at election meetings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29714&sectionno=127&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who at a public meeting to which this`
  line `section applies acts, or incites others to act, in a disorderly manner for the purpose of preventing the`
  line `transaction of the business for which the meeting was called together, ^1[shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^2[six months or with fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees], or with both.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) An offence punishable under sub-section (1) shall be cognizable.]`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies to any public meeting of a political character held in any constituency`
  line `between the date of the issue of a notification under this Act calling upon the constituency to elect a`
  line `member or members and the date on which such election is held.`
  line
  line `(3) If any police officer reasonably suspects any person of committing an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1), he may, if requested so to do by the chairman of the meeting, require that person to`
  line `declare to him immediately his name and address and, if that person refuses or fails so to declare his name`
  line `and address, or if the police officer reasonably suspects him of giving a false name or address, the police`
  line `officer may arrest him without warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1989, s. 14, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_127_a:
  sectionId (29715)
  sectionNo 127A
  orderNo 150
  title `Restrictions on the printing of pamphlets, posters, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 26 (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29715&sectionno=127A&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_127_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[127A. Restrictions on the printing of pamphlets, posters, etc,--(1) No person shall print or`
  line `publish, or cause to be printed or published, any election pamphlet or poster which does not bear on its`
  line `face the names and addresses of the printer and the publisher thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall print or cause to be printed any election pamphlet or poster--`
  line
  line `(a) unless a declaration as to the identity of the publisher thereof, signed by him and attested by`
  line `two persons to whom he is personally known, is delivered by him to the printer in duplicate; and`
  line
  line `(b) unless, within a reasonable time after the printing of the document, one copy of the`
  line `declaration is sent by the printer, together with one copy of the document,--`
  line
  line `(i) where it is printed in the capital of the State, to the Chief Electoral Officer; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, to the district magistrate of the district in which it is printed.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) any process for multiplying copies of a document, other than copying it by hand, shall be`
  line `deemed to be printing and the expression "printer" shall be construed accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(b) "election pamphlet or poster" means any printed pamphlet, hand-bill or other document`
  line `distributed for the purpose of promoting or prejudicing the election of a candidate or group of`
  line `candidates or any placard or poster having reference to an election, but does not include any handbill,`
  line `placard or poster merely announcing the date, time, place and other particulars of an election`
  line `meeting or routine instructions to election agents or workers.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who contravenes any of the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend`
  line `to two thousand rupees, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (29716)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 151
  title `Maintenance of Secrecy of voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2003, s. 5 (w.e.f. 28-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29716&sectionno=128&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer, clerk, agent or other person who`
  line `performs any duty in connection with the recording or counting of votes at an election shall maintain, and`
  line `aid in maintaining, the secrecy of the voting and shall not (except for some purpose authorised by or`
  line `under any law) communicate to any person any information calculated to violate such secrecy:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to such officer, clerk, agent or other`
  line `person who performs any such duty at an election to fill a seat or seats in the Council of States.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (29717)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 152
  title `Officers, etc., at elections not to act for candidates or to influence voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29717&sectionno=129&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person who is ^1[a district election officer or a returning officer], or an assistant returning officer, or a presiding or`
  line `polling officer at an election, or an officer or clerk appointed by the returning officer for the presiding`
  line `officer to perform any duty in connection with an election shall in the conduct or the management of the`
  line `election do any act (other than the giving of vote) for the furtherance of the prospects of the election of a`
  line candidate.
  line
  line `(2) No such person as aforesaid, and no member of a police force, shall endeavour—`
  line
  line `(a) to persuade any person to give his vote at an election, or`
  line
  line `(b) to dissuade any person from giving his vote at an election, or`
  line
  line `(c) to influence the voting of any person at an election in any manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (3) shall be cognizable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 55, for "a returning officer" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 55 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (29732)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 153
  title `Prohibition of canvassing in or near polling stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for "one hundred yards" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29732&sectionno=130&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, on the date or`
  line `dates on which a poll is taken at any polling station, commit any of the following acts within the polling`
  line `station or in any public or private place within a distance of ^1[one hundred metres] of the polling station,`
  line `namely:`
  line
  line `(a) canvassing for votes; or`
  line
  line `(b) soliciting the vote of any elector; or`
  line
  line `(c) persuading any elector not to vote for any particular candidate; or`
  line
  line `(d) persuading any elector not to vote at the election; or`
  line
  line `(e) exhibiting any notice or sign (other than an official notice) relating to the election.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) An offence punishable under this section shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (29733)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 154
  title `Penalty for disorderly conduct in or near polling stations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29733&sectionno=131&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, on the date`
  line `or dates on which a poll is taken at any polling station,—`
  line
  line `(a) use or operate within or at the entrance of the polling station, or in any public or private place`
  line `in the neighbourhood thereof, any apparatus for amplifying or reproducing the human voice, such as a`
  line `megaphone or a loudspeaker, or`
  line
  line `(b) shout, or otherwise act in a disorderly manner, within or at the entrance of the polling station`
  line `or in any public or private place in the neighbourhood thereof,`
  line
  line `so as to cause annoyance to any person visiting the polling station for the poll, or so as to interfere with`
  line `the work of the officers and other persons on duty at the polling station.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes, or wilfully aids or abets the contravention of, the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months or with fine or`
  line `with both.`
  line
  line `(3) If the presiding officer of a polling station has reason to believe that any person is committing or`
  line `has committed an offence punishable under this section, he may direct any police officer to arrest such`
  line `person, and thereupon the police officer shall arrest him.`
  line
  line `(4) Any police officer may take such steps, and use such force, as may be reasonably necessary for`
  line `preventing any contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1), and may seize any apparatus used for`
  line `such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (29734)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 155
  title `Penalty for misconduct at the polling station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29734&sectionno=132&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who during the hours fixed for`
  line `the poll at any polling station misconducts himself or fails to obey the lawful directions of the presiding`
  line `officer may be removed from the polling station by the presiding officer or by any police officer on duty`
  line `or by any person authorised in this behalf by such presiding officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers conferred by sub-section (1) shall not be exercised so as to prevent any elector who is`
  line `otherwise entitled to vote at a polling station from having an opportunity of voting at that station.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person who has been so removed from a polling station re-enters the polling station without`
  line `the permission of the presiding officer, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (3) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132_a:
  sectionId (29735)
  sectionNo 132A
  orderNo 156
  title `Penalty for failure to observe procedure for voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29735&sectionno=132A&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_132_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[132A. Penalty for failure to observe procedure for voting--If any elector to whom a ballot`
  line `paper has been issued, refused to observe the procedure prescribed for voting the ballot paper issued to`
  line `him shall be liable for cancellation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (29736)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 157
  title `Penalty for illegal hiring or procuring of conveyance at elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 12, for section 133 (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29736&sectionno=133&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `^1[133. Penalty for illegal hiring or procuring of conveyance at elections.--If any person is guilty`
  line `of any such corrupt practice as is specified in clause (5) of section 123 at or in connection with an`
  line `election, he shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months and with fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (29737)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 158
  title `Breaches of official duty in connection with elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29737&sectionno=134&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person to whom this section`
  line `applies is without reasonable cause guilty of any act or omission in breach of his official duty, he shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) An offence punishable under sub-section (1) shall be cognizable.]`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against any such person for damages in respect of any`
  line `such act or omission as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons to whom this section applies are the ^2*** ^3[district election officers, returning`
  line `officers], assistant returning officers, presiding officers, polling officers and any other person appointed to`
  line `perform any duty in connection with ^4*** the receipt of nominations or withdrawal of candidatures, or the`
  line `recording or counting of votes at an election; and the expression official duty shall for the purposes of`
  line `this section be construed accordingly, but shall not include duties imposed otherwise than by or under this`
  line `Act ^2***.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 58 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 37 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 58, for "returning officers" (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line `4. The words "the preparation of an electoral roll" omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 37 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_134_a:
  sectionId (29738)
  sectionNo 134A
  orderNo 159
  title `Penalty for Government servants for acting as election agent, polling agent or counting agent`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 59 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29738&sectionno=134A&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_134_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[134A. Penalty for Government servants for acting as election agent, polling agent or counting`
  line `agent.--If any person in the service of the Government acts as an election agent or a polling agent or a`
  line `counting agent of a candidate at an election, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three months, or with fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_134_b:
  sectionId (29739)
  sectionNo 134B
  orderNo 160
  title `Prohibition of going armed to or near a polling station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29739&sectionno=134B&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_134_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[134B. Prohibition of going armed to or near a polling station.--(1) No person, other than the`
  line `returning officer, the presiding officer, any police officer and any other person appointed to maintain`
  line `peace and order at a polling station who is on duty at the polling station, shall, on a polling day, go armed`
  line `with arms, as defined in the Arms Act, 1959 (54 of 1959), of any kind within the neighbourhood of a`
  line `polling station.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Arms Act, 1959 (54 of 1959), where a person is`
  line `convicted of an offience under this section, the arms as defined in the said Act found in his possession`
  line `shall be liable to confiscation and the licence granted in relation to such arms shall be deemed to have`
  line `been revoked under section 17 of that Act.`
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (2) shall be cognizable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (29740)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 161
  title `Removal of ballot papers from polling station to be an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 14, for "fraudulently" (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29740&sectionno=135&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who at any`
  line `election ^1[unauthorisedly] takes, or attempts to take, a ballot paper out of a polling station, or wilfully aids`
  line `or abets the doing of any such act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If the presiding officer of a polling station has reason to believe that any person is committing or`
  line `has committed an offence punishable under sub-section (1), such officer may, before such person leaves`
  line `the polling station, arrest or direct a police officer to arrest such person and may search such person or`
  line `cause him to be searched by a police officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that when it is necessary to cause a woman to be searched, the search shall be made by`
  line `another woman with strict regard to decency.`
  line
  line `(3) Any ballot paper found upon the person arrested on search shall be made over for safe custody to`
  line `a police officer by the presiding officer, or when the search is made by a police officer, shall be kept by`
  line `such officer in safe custody.`
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (1) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_a:
  sectionId (29741)
  sectionNo 135A
  orderNo 162
  title `Offence of booth capturing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29741&sectionno=135A&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_135_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[135A. Offence of booth capturing.--^2[(1)] Whoever commits an offence of booth capturing shall`
  line `be punishable with imprisonment for a term which ^3[shall not be less than one year but which may extend`
  line `extend to three years and with fine, and where such offence is committed by a person in the service of the`
  line `Government, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years`
  line `but which may extend to five years and with fine.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of ^3[this sub-section and section 20B], booth capturing includes,`
  line `among other things, all or any of the following activities, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) seizure of a polling station or a place fixed for the poll by any person or persons, making`
  line `polling authorities surrender the ballot papers or voting machines and doing of any other Act which`
  line `affects the orderly conduct of elections;`
  line
  line `(b) taking possession of a polling station or a place fixed for the poll by any person or persons,`
  line `and allowing only his or their own supporters to exercise their right to vote and ^4[prevent others from`
  line `free exercise of their right to vote];`
  line
  line `(c)^5[coercing or intimidating or threatening directly or indirectly], any elector and preventing him`
  line `him from going to the polling station or a place fixed for the poll to cast his vote;`
  line
  line `(d) seizure of a place for counting of votes by any person or persons, making the counting`
  line `authorities surrender the ballot papers or voting machines and the doing of anything which affects the`
  line `orderly counting of votes;`
  line
  line `(e) doing by any person in the service of Government, of all or any of the aforesaid activities or`
  line `aiding or conniving at, any such activity in the furtherance of the prospects of the election of a`
  line candidate.]
  line
  line `^6[(2) An offence punishable under sub-section (1) shall be cognizable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1989, s. 15 (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  line `2. Section 135A renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 21 of 1996, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15, bid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "this section" (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "threatening" (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_135_b:
  sectionId (29742)
  sectionNo 135B
  orderNo 163
  title `Grant of paid holiday to employees on the day of poll`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 16,ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1996),`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29742&sectionno=135B&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_135_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[135B. Grant of paid holiday to employees on the day of poll.--(1) Every person employed in any`
  line `any business, trade, industrial undertaking or any other establishment and entitled to vote at an election to`
  line `the House of the People or the Legislative Assembly of a State shall, on the day of poll, be granted a`
  line holiday.
  line
  line `(2) No deduction or abatement of the wages of any such person shall be made on account of a holiday`
  line `having been granted in accordance with sub-section (1) and if such person is employed on the basis that`
  line `he would not ordinarily receive wages for such a day, he shall nonetheless be paid for such day the wages`
  line `he would have drawn had not a holiday been granted to him on that day.`
  line
  line `(3) If an employer contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), then such`
  line `employer shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) This section shall not apply to any elector whose absence may cause danger or substantial loss in`
  line `respect of the employment in which he is engaged.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_c:
  sectionId (29743)
  sectionNo 135C
  orderNo 164
  title `Liquor not to be sold, given or distributed on polling day`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29743&sectionno=135C&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_135_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) No spirituous, fermented or`
  line `intoxicating liquors or other substances of a like nature shall be sold, given or distributed at a hotel, eating`
  line `house, tavern, shop or any other place, public or private, within a polling area during the period of`
  line `forty-eight hours ending with the hour fixed for the conclusion of the poll for any election in that polling`
  line area.
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine, which may extend to two thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person is convicted of an offence under this section, the spirituous, fermented, or`
  line `intoxicating liquors or other substances of a like nature found in his possession shall be liable to`
  line `confiscation and the same shall be disposed of in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (29744)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 165
  title `Other offences and penalties therefor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29744&sectionno=136&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be guilty of an electoral offence if`
  line `at any election he--`
  line
  line `(a) fraudulently defaces or fraudulently destroys any nomination paper; or`
  line
  line `(b) fraudulently defaces, destroys or removes any list, notice or other document affixed by or`
  line `under the authority of returning officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) fraudulently defaces or fraudulently destroys any ballot paper or the official mark on any`
  line `ballot paper or any declaration of identity or official envelop used in connection with voting by postal`
  line `ballot; or`
  line
  line `(d) without due authority supplies any ballot paper to any person ^1[or receives any ballot paper`
  line `from any person or is in possession of any ballot paper]; or`
  line
  line `(e) fraudulently puts into any ballot box anything other than the ballot paper which he is`
  line `authorised by law to put in; or`
  line
  line `(f) without due authority destroys, takes, opens or otherwise interferes with any ballot box or`
  line `ballot papers than in use for the purposes of the election; or`
  line
  line `(g) fraudulently or without due authority, as the case may be, attempts to do any of the foregoing`
  line `acts or wilfully aids or abets the doing of any such acts.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person guilty of an electoral offence under this section shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is a returning officer or an assistant returning officer or a presiding officer at a polling`
  line `station or any other officer or clerk employed on official duty in connection with the election, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is any other person, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, a person shall be deemed to be on official duty if his duty is to`
  line `take part in the conduct of an election or part of an election including the counting of votes or to be`
  line `responsible after an election for the used ballot papers and other documents in connection with such`
  line `election, but the expression "official duty" shall not include any duty imposed otherwise than by or under`
  line `this Act ^2***.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (2) shall be cognizable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 70 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 38 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 60, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
