obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (29756)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 176
  title `Powers of Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 17 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-9-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29756&sectionno=146&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where in connection with the tendering of any opinion`
  line `to the President under article 103 or, as the case may be, under sub-section (4) of section 14 of the`
  line `Government of Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963), or to the Governor under article 192, the`
  line `Election Commission considers it necessary or proper to make an inquiry, and the Commission is`
  line `satisfied that on the basis of the affidavits filed and the documents produced in such inquiry by the parties`
  line `concerned of their own accord, it cannot come to a decisive opinion on the matter which is being inquired`
  line `into, the Commission shall have, for the purposes of such inquiry, the powers of a civil court, while trying`
  line `a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or a copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall also have the power to require any person, subject to any privilege which`
  line `may be claimed by that person under any law for the time being in force, to furnish information on such`
  line `points or matters as in the opinion of the Commission may be useful for, or relevant to, the subject matter`
  line `of the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court and when any such offence, as is described in`
  line `section 175, section 178, section 179, section 180 or section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), is`
  line `committed in the view or presence of the Commission, the Commission may after recording the facts`
  line `constituting the offence and the statement of the accused as provided for in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), forward the case to a magistrate having jurisdiction to try the same and the`
  line `magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the complaint against the`
  line `accused as if the case had been forwarded to him under section 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(4) Any proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_146_a:
  sectionId (29757)
  sectionNo 146A
  orderNo 177
  title `Statements made by persons to the Election Commission`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29757&sectionno=146A&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_146_a_content:
  string
  line `No statement made by a person`
  line `in the course of giving evidence before the Election Commission shall subject him to, or be used against`
  line `him in, any civil or criminal proceeding except a prosecution for giving false evidence by such statement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the statement--`
  line
  line `(a) is made in reply to a question which he is required by the Commission to answer, or`
  line
  line `(b) is relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146_b:
  sectionId (29758)
  sectionNo 146B
  orderNo 178
  title `Procedure to be followed by the Election Commission`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29758&sectionno=146B&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_146_b_content:
  string
  line `The Election Commission shall`
  line `have the power to regulate its own procedure (including the fixing of places and times of its sittings and`
  line `deciding whether to sit in public or in private).`
obj_root_law_sections_146_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146_c:
  sectionId (29759)
  sectionNo 146C
  orderNo 179
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29759&sectionno=146C&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_146_c_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Commission or any person acting under the direction of the Commission in respect of`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the foregoing provisions of`
  line `this Chapter or of any order made thereunder or in respect of the tendering of any opinion by the`
  line `Commission to the President or, as the case may be, to the Governor or in respect of the publication, by or`
  line `under the authority of the Commission of any such opinion, paper or proceedings].`
obj_root_law_sections_146_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (29760)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 180
  title `Casual vacancies in the Council of States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29760&sectionno=147&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] When before the expiration of the term of`
  line `office of a member elected to the Council of States, his seat becomes vacant or is declared vacant or his`
  line `election to the Council of States is declared void, the Election Commission shall by a notification in the`
  line `Gazette of India call upon the elected members of the Legislative Assembly or the members of the`
  line `electoral college concerned ^2***, as the case may be, to elect a person for the purpose of filling the`
  line `vacancy so caused before such date as may be specified in the notification and the provisions of this Act`
  line `and of the rules and orders made thereunder shall apply, as far as may be, in relation to the election of a`
  line `member to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) As soon as may be after the date of commencement of the Constitution (Seventh Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1956, bye-elections shall be held to fill the vacancies existing on that date in the seats allotted to the`
  line `States of Assam, Orissa and Uttar Pradesh and the ^4[Union territories of Delhi, Himachal Pradesh and`
  line Manipur.]]
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 147 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `2. The words "or the elected members of the Coorg Legislative Council" omitted by Act 49 of 1951, s. 44 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 6-9-1951).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
  line
  line `4. Now the National Capital territory of Delhi and the States of Himachal Pradesh and Manipur.`
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (29761)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 181
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29761&sectionno=148&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `[Casual vacancies in the electoral colleges for certain Union territories.] Omitted by the`
  line `Territorial Councils Act, 1956 (103 of 1956), s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-1-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (29762)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 182
  title `Casual vacancies in the House of the People.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29762&sectionno=149&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the seat of a member elected to the`
  line `House of the People becomes vacant or is declared vacant or his election to the House of the People is`
  line `declared void, the Election Commission shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), by a`
  line `notification in the Gazette of India, call upon the parliamentary constituency concerned to elect a person`
  line `for the purpose of filling the vacancy so caused before such date as may be specified in the notification,`
  line `and the provisions of this Act and of the rules and orders made thereunder shall apply, as far as may be, in`
  line `relation to the election of a member to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) If the vacancy so caused be a vacancy in a seat reserved in any such constituency for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or for any Scheduled Tribes, the notification issued under sub-section (1) shall specify`
  line `that the person to fill that seat shall belong to the Scheduled Castes or to such Scheduled Tribes, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (29763)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 183
  title `Casual vacancies in the State Legislative Assemblies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29763&sectionno=150&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `When the seat of a member elected to`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of a State becomes vacant or is declared vacant or his election to the Legislative`
  line `Assembly is declared void, the Election Commission shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), by`
  line `a notification in the Official Gazette, call upon the Assembly constituency concerned to elect a person for the purpose of filling the vacancy so caused before such date as may be specified in the notification, and`
  line `the provisions of this Act and of the rules and orders made thereunder shall apply, as far as may be, in`
  line `relation to the election of a member to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) If the vacancy so caused be a vacancy in a seat reserved in any such constituency for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or for any Scheduled Tribes, the notification issued under sub-section (1) shall specify`
  line `that the person to fill that seat shall belong to the Scheduled Castes or to such Scheduled Tribes, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (29764)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 184
  title `Casual vacancies in the State Legislative Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29764&sectionno=151&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `When before the expiration of the term`
  line `of office of a member elected to the Legislative Council of a State, his seat becomes vacant or is declared`
  line `vacant or his election to the Legislative Council is declared void, the Election Commission shall, by a`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, call upon the Council constituency concerned or the members of the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of the State, as the case may be, to elect a person for the purpose of filling the`
  line `vacancy so caused, before such date as may be specified in the notification, and the provisions of this Act`
  line `and of the rules and orders made thereunder shall apply, as far as may be, in relation to the election of a`
  line `member to fill such vacancy.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151_a:
  sectionId (29765)
  sectionNo 151A
  orderNo 185
  title `Time limit for filling vacancies referred to in sections 147, 149, 150 and 151.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29765&sectionno=151A&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_151_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[151A. Time limit for filling vacancies referred to in sections 147, 149, 150`
  line `and 151.—Notwithstanding anything contained in section 147, section 149, section 150 and section 151,`
  line `a bye-election for filling any vacancy referred to in any of the said sections shall be held within a period`
  line `of six months from the date of the occurrence of the vacancy:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply if—`
  line
  line `(a) the remainder of the term of a member in relation to a vacancy is less than one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Election Commission in consultation with the Central Government certifies that it is`
  line `difficult to hold the bye-election within the said period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (29766)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 186
  title `List of members of the State Legislative Assemblies and electoral colleges to be maintained by the returning officers concerned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29766&sectionno=152&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) The returning officer for an election by the elected members of`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of a State to fill a seat or seats in the Council of States or for an election, by the`
  line `members of the Legislative Assembly of a State to fill a seat or seats in the Legislative Council of the`
  line `State shall, for the purposes of such election maintain in his office in the prescribed manner and form a`
  line `list of elected members or a list of members, as the case may be, of that Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `(2) The returning officer for an election by the members of the electoral college for a ^1[Union`
  line `territory] ^2*** ^3*** to fill a seat or seats in the Council of States shall, for the purposes of such election,`
  line `maintain in his office in the prescribed manner and form a list of members of that electoral college ^3***.`
  line
  line `(3) Copies of the lists referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be made available for sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part C State".`
  line `2. The words "or group of such States" omitted by Act 27 of 1956, s. 77 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  line `3. Certain words omitted by Act 49 of 1951, s. 44 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 6-9-1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (29767)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 187
  title `Extension of time for completion of election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 78, for section 153 (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29767&sectionno=153&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `^1[153. Extension of time for completion of election.--It shall be competent for the Election`
  line `Commission for reasons which it considers sufficient, to extend the time for the completion of any`
  line `election by making necessary amendments in the notification issued by it under section 30 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 39.]`
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (29768)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 188
  title `Term of office of members of the Council of States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29768&sectionno=154&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (2) and (2A), the term of office of a member of the Council of States, other than a member`
  line `chosen to fill a casual vacancy, shall be six years.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^2*** Upon the first constitution of the Council of States the President shall, after consultation with`
  line `the Election Commission, make by order such provision as he thinks fit for curtailing the term of office of some of the members then chosen in order that, as nearly as may be, one-third of the members holding`
  line `seats of each class shall retire in every second year thereafter.`
  line
  line `^3[(2A) In order that, as nearly as may be, one-third of the members may retire on the second day of`
  line `April, 1958, and on the expiration of every second year thereafter, the President shall, as soon as may be`
  line `after the commencement of the Constitution (Seventh Amendment) Act, 1956, after consultation with the`
  line `Election Commission, make by order such provisions as he thinks fit in regard to the terms of office of`
  line `the members elected under sub-section (2) of section 147.]`
  line
  line `(3) A member chosen to fill a casual vacancy shall be chosen to serve for the remainder of his`
  line `predecessor's term of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for sub-section (1).`
  line `2. Certain words omitted, ibid.`
  line `3. Ins. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (29769)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 189
  title `Commencement of the term of office of members of the Council of States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29769&sectionno=155&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of`
  line `office of a member of the Council of States whose name is required to be notified in the Official Gazette`
  line `under section 71 shall begin on the date of such notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of a member of the Council of States whose name is not required to be notified`
  line `under section 71 shall begin on the date of publication in the Official Gazette of the declaration`
  line `containing the name of such person as elected under section 67 or of the notification issued under`
  line `sub-clause (a) of clause (1) of article 80 or under any other provision announcing the nomination of such`
  line `person to the Council of States, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (29770)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 190
  title `Term of office of members of State Legislative Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or the Rajpramukh, as the case may be" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No.2) Order, 1956, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29770&sectionno=156&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of a`
  line `member of the Legislative Council of a State, other than a member chosen to fill a casual vacancy, shall`
  line `be six years, but upon the first constitution of the Council the Governor ^1*** shall, after consultation with`
  line `the Election Commission, make by order such provision as he thinks fit for curtailing the term of office of`
  line `some of the members then chosen in order that, as nearly as may be, one-third of the members holding`
  line `seats of each class shall retire in every second year thereafter.`
  line
  line `(2) A member chosen to fill a casual vacancy shall be chosen to serve for the remainder of his`
  line `predecessor's term of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (29771)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 191
  title `Commencement of the term of office of members of the Legislative Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 1956, s. 79, for "section 75" (w.e.f. 28-8-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29771&sectionno=157&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term`
  line `of office of a member of the Legislative Council of a State whose name is required to be notified in the`
  line `Official Gazette under ^1[section 74] shall begin on the date of such notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of a member of the Legislative Council of a State whose name is not required`
  line `to be notified under ^1[section 74] shall begin on the date of publication in the Official Gazette of the`
  line `declaration containing the name of such person as elected under section 67 or of the notification issued`
  line `under sub-clause (e) of clause (3) of article 171, announcing the nomination of such person to the`
  line `Council, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (29772)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 192
  title `Return or forfeiture of candidate’s deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 39, for section 158 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29772&sectionno=158&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `^1[158. Return or forfeiture of candidate's deposit.--(1) The deposit made under section 34 or`
  line `under that section read with sub-section (2) of section 39 shall either be returned to the person making it`
  line `or his legal representative or be forfeited to the appropriate authority in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Except in cases hereafter mentioned in this section, the deposit shall be returned as soon as`
  line `practicable after the result of the election is declared.`
  line
  line `(3) If the candidate is not shown in the list of contesting candidates, or if he dies before the`
  line `commencement of the poll, the deposit shall be returned as soon as practicable after the publication of the`
  line `list or after his death, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), the deposit shall be forfeited if at an election where a`
  line `poll has been taken, the candidate is not elected and the number of valid votes polled by him does not`
  line `exceed one-sixth of the total number of valid votes polled by all the candidates or in the case of election of more than one member at the election, one-sixth of the total number of valid votes so polled divided by`
  line `the number of members to be elected:`
  line
  line `Provided that where at an election held in, accordance with the system of proportional representation`
  line `by means of the single transferable vote, a candidate is not elected, the deposit made by him shall be`
  line `forfeited if he does not get more than one-sixth of the number of votes prescribed in this behalf as`
  line `sufficient to secure the return of a candidate.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything in sub-sections (2), (3) and (4),`
  line
  line `(a) if at a general election, the candidate is a contesting candidate in more than one Parliamentary`
  line `constituency or in more than one assembly constituency, not more than one of the deposits shall be`
  line `returned, and the other shall be forfeited.]`
  line
  line `(b) if the candidate is a contesting candidate at an election in more than one council constituency`
  line `or at an election in a Council constituency and at an election by the members of the State Legislative`
  line `Assembly to fill seats in the Legislative Council, not more than one of the deposits shall be returned,`
  line `and the others shall be forfeited.]`
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (29773)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 193
  title `Staff or certain authorities to be made available for election work`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1998, s. 2, for section 159 (w.e.f. 23-12-1997).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29773&sectionno=159&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `^1[159. Staff of certain authorities to be made available for election work.--(1) The authorities`
  line `specified in sub-section (2) shall, when so requested by a Regional Commissioner appointed under`
  line `clause (4) of article 324 or the Chief Electoral Officer of the State, make available to any returning officer`
  line `such staff as may be necessary for the performance of any duties in connection with an election.`
  line
  line `(2) The following shall be the authorities for the purposes of sub-section (1), namely:`
  line
  line `(i) every local authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) every university established or incorporated by or under a Central, Provincial or State Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) a Government company as defined in section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(iv) any other institution, concern or undertaking which is established by or under a Central,`
  line `Provincial or State Act or which is controlled, or financed wholly or substantially by funds provided,`
  line `directly or indirectly, by the Central Government or a State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (29774)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 194
  title `Requisitioning of premises, vehicles, etc., for election purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29774&sectionno=160&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the State`
  line `Government that in connection with an election held within the State`
  line
  line `^1[(a) any premises are needed or are likely to be needed for the purpose of being used as polling`
  line `stations, for counting, for storage of ballot boxes, voting machines (including voter verifiable paper`
  line `audit trail) and poll related material after a poll has been taken, accommodation for security forces`
  line `and polling personnel; or]`
  line
  line `(b) any vehicle, vessel or animal is needed or is likely to be needed for the purpose of transport`
  line `of ballot boxes to or from any polling station, or transport of members of the police force for`
  line `maintaining order during the conduct of such election, or transport of any officer or other person for`
  line `performance of any duties in connection with such election,`
  line
  line `that Government may by order in writing requisition such premises, or such vehicle, vessel or animal, as`
  line `the case may be, and may make such further orders as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient in`
  line `connection with the requisitioning:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that such premises shall be requisitioned after the issuance of the notification by the`
  line `Election Commission under section 30 for such election till the date notified under clause (e) thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided further that] no vehicle, vessel or animal which is being lawfully used by a candidate or his agent for`
  line `any purpose connected with the election of such candidate shall be requisitioned under this sub-section`
  line `until the completion of the poll at such election.`
  line
  line `(2) The requisition shall be effected by an order in writing addressed to the person deemed by the`
  line `State Government to be the owner or person in possession of the property, and such order shall be served`
  line `in the prescribed manner on the person to whom it is addressed.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever any property is requisitioned under sub-section (1), the period of such requisition shall`
  line `not extend beyond the period for which such property is required for any of the purposes mentioned in`
  line `that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section,`
  line
  line `(a) premises means any land, building or part of a building and includes a hut, shed or other`
  line `structure or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) vehicle means any vehicle used or capable of being used for the purpose of road transport,`
  line `whether propelled by mechanical power or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 2021, s. 7, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-8-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "Provided that" (w.e.f. 1-8-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (29775)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 195
  title `Payment of compensation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29775&sectionno=161&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever in pursuance of section 160 the State Government`
  line `requisitions any premises, there shall be paid to the persons interested compensation the amount of which`
  line `shall be determined by taking into consideration the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the rent payable in respect of the premises or if no rent is so payable, the rent payable for`
  line `similar premises in the locality;`
  line
  line `(ii) if in consequence of the requisition of the premises the person interested is compelled to`
  line `change his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses (if any) incidental to such change:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person interested being aggrieved by the amount of compensation so`
  line `determined makes an application within the prescribed time to the State Government for referring the`
  line `matter to an arbitrator, the amount of compensation to be paid shall be such as the arbitrator appointed in`
  line `this behalf by the State Government may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where there is any dispute as to the title to receive the compensation or as to the`
  line `apportionment of the amount of compensation, it shall be referred by the State Government to an`
  line `arbitrator appointed in this behalf by that Government for determination, and shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with the decision of such arbitrator.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section, the expression "person interested" means the person who was in`
  line `actual possession of the premises requisitioned under section 160 immediately before the requisition, or`
  line `where no person was in such actual possession, the owner of such premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever in pursuance of section 160 the State Government requisitions any vehicle, vessel or`
  line `animal, there shall be paid to the owner thereof compensation the amount of which shall be determined by`
  line `the State Government on the basis of fares or rates prevailing in the locality for the hire of such vehicle,`
  line `vessel or animal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the owner of such vehicle, vessel or animal being aggrieved by the amount of`
  line `compensation so determined makes an application within the prescribed time to the State Government for`
  line `referring the matter to an arbitrator, the amount of compensation to be paid shall be such as the arbitrator`
  line `appointed in this behalf by the State Government may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where immediately before the requisitioning the vehicle or vessel was by virtue`
  line `of a hire-purchase agreement in the possession of a person other than the owner, the amount determined`
  line `under this sub-section as the total compensation payable in respect of the requisition shall be apportioned`
  line `between that person and the owner in such manner as they may agree upon, and in default of agreement,`
  line `in such manner as an arbitrator appointed by the State Government in this behalf may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (29776)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 196
  title `Power to obtain information`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29776&sectionno=162&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may with a view to requisitioning any`
  line `property under section 160 or determining the compensation payable under section 161, by order, require`
  line `any person to furnish to such authority as may be specified in the order such information in his possession`
  line `relating to such property as may be so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (29777)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 197
  title `Powers of entry into and inspection of premises, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29777&sectionno=163&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the State Government may enter into any premises and inspect such premises and any vehicle,`
  line `vessel or animal therein for the purpose of determining whether, and if so in what manner, an order under`
  line `section 160 should be made in relation to such premises, vehicle, vessel or animal, or with a view to`
  line `securing compliance with any order made under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section the expressions premises and vehicle have the same meanings as in`
  line `section 160.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (29778)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 198
  title `Eviction from requisitioned premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29778&sectionno=164&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person remaining in possession of any`
  line `requisitioned premises in contravention of any order made under section 160 may be summarily evicted`
  line `from the premises by any officer empowered by the State Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer so empowered may, after giving to any woman not appearing in public reasonable`
  line `warning and facility to withdraw, remove or open any lock or bolt or break open any door of any building`
  line `or do any other act necessary for effecting such eviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (29779)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 199
  title `Release of premises from requisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29779&sectionno=165&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any premises requisitioned under`
  line `section 160 are to be released from requisition, the possession thereof shall be delivered to the person`
  line `from whom possession was taken at the time when the premises were requisitioned, or if there were no`
  line `such person, to the person deemed by the State Government to be the owner of such premises, and such`
  line `delivery of possession shall be a full discharge of the State Government from all liabilities in respect of`
  line `such delivery, but shall not prejudice any rights in respect of the premises which any other person may be`
  line `entitled by due process of law to enforce against the person to whom possession of the premises is so`
  line delivered.
  line
  line `(2) Where the person to whom possession of any premises requisitioned under section 160 is to be`
  line `given under sub-section (1) cannot be found or is not readily ascertainable or has no agent or any other`
  line `person empowered to accept delivery on his behalf, the State Government shall cause a notice declaring`
  line `that such premises are released from requisition to be affixed on some conspicuous part of such premises`
  line `and publish the notice in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) When a notice referred to in sub-section (2) is published in the Official Gazette, the premises`
  line `specified in such notice shall cease to be subject to requisition on and from the date of such publication`
  line `and be deemed to have been delivered to the person entitled to possession thereof; and the State`
  line `Government shall not be liable for any compensation or other claim in respect of such premises for any`
  line `period after the said date.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (29780)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 200
  title `Delegation of functions of the State Government with regard to requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29780&sectionno=166&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `The State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any powers conferred or any duty`
  line `imposed on that Government by any of the provisions of sections 160 to 165 shall, under such conditions,`
  line `if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercised or discharged by such officer or class of officers`
  line `as may be so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (29781)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 201
  title `Penalty for contravention of any order regarding requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29781&sectionno=167&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `If any person contravenes`
  line `any order made under section 160 or section 162, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (29782)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 202
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29782&sectionno=168&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `[Special provisions with respect to Rulers of former Indian States.] Omitted by Rulers of Indian`
  line `States (Abolition of Privileges) Act, 1972 (54 of 1972), s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-9-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (29783)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 203
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29783&sectionno=169&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consulting the Election`
  line `Commission, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules^1for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) the form of affidavit under sub-section (2) of section 33A;]`
  line
  line `^3[(aa)] the duties of presiding officers and polling officers at polling stations;`
  line
  line `^4[(aaa) the form of contribution report;]`
  line
  line `(b) the checking of voters by reference to the electoral roll;`
  line
  line `^4[(bb) the manner of allocation of equitable sharing of time on the cable television network and`
  line `other electronic media;]`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which votes are to be given both generally and in the case of illiterate voters or`
  line `voters under physical or other disability;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which votes are to be given by a presiding officer, polling officer, polling agent`
  line `or any other person, who being an elector for a constituency is authorised or appointed for duty at a`
  line `polling station at which he is not entitled to vole;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure to be followed in respect of the lender of vote by a person representing himself`
  line `to be an elector after another person has voted as such elector;`
  line
  line `^5[(ee) the manner of giving and recording of voles by means of voting machines and the`
  line `procedure as to voting to be followed at polling stations where such machines are used;]`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure as to voting to be followed at elections held in accordance with the system of`
  line `proportional representation by means of the single transferable vote;`
  line
  line `(g) the scrutiny and counting of votes including cases in which a recount of the votes may be`
  line `made before the declaration of the result of the election;`
  line
  line `^5[(gg) the procedure as to counting of votes recorded by means of voting machines;]`
  line
  line `(h) the safe custody of ^6[ballot boxes, voting machines], ballot papers and other election papers,`
  line `the period for which such papers shall be preserved and the inspection and production of such papers;`
  line
  line `^7[(hh) the material to be supplied by the Government to the candidates of recognised political`
  line `parties at any election to be held for the purposes of constituting the House of the People or the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of a State;]`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter required to be prescribed by this Act.`
  line
  line `^8[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^9[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made,] the rule shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to validity of anything previously done under the rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See the Conduct of Election Rules, 1961.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 72 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 24-8-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (a) renumbered as (aa) by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-8-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 46 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 11-9-2003).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 2003, s. 6 (w.e.f. 11-9-2003).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 1 of 1989, s. 16 (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 29, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (29784)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 204
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542&sectionId=29784&sectionno=170&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_81_00001_195143_1517807327542
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to question the`
  line `legality of any action taken or of any decision given by the returning officer or by any other person`
  line `appointed under this Act in connection with an election.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
